blurb_text: The 2019 federal election was held on 18 May 2019. In Western Australia, the elected candidates were Linda Reynolds (Liberal), Patrick Dodson (Australian Labor Party), Slade Brockman (Liberal), Matt O'Sullivan (Liberal), Louise Pratt (Australian Labor Party), and Jordon Steele-John (The Greens (WA)).
